recordings.loc: Rivas, Pérez Zeledón, San José Province
recordings.rmk: Have seen multiple quetzals in Cloudbridge Nature Reserve who make this call. I haven’t heard it anywhere else (mainly Monteverde which is the other place I’ve seen quetzals). I’ve heard them make these sounds here nearly always I’ve seen them (5 times), both by males and females. They still make the other regular sounds but they also do these, which are always a rising whistle with a slight dip in pitch towards the end. I’ve heard them multiple times only making this noise and not the others, and have seen it from several individuals. I have not been able to find this sound in other recordings. I wonder if they make this sound in other places or if it’s just here in Cloudbridge/Talamanca
